				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$_{4}$$\end{document} surfaces. This will be addressed in future model studies where additional molecular water adsorption will be taken into account. Without solvent effects, neither the most stable Zn-rich model nor the most stable Fe-rich model have suitable band positions for solar hydrogen production. We therefore conclude that ZnFe2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
